+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01WSup1gAnmD3NV1apN8Fpgg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XmFdoWvZYAtrtFqqn2z1To","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-plugin-marketplace.md","content":"# Plugin Marketplace Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a plugin marketplace system with 5 modules (registry, resolver, runner, reviews, deps) and an integration layer.\n\n**Architecture:** Each module is a standalone service in its own directory under `src/`. They share only types from `src/types.ts`. The integration layer in `src/index.ts` composes all services via `createMarketplace()`.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Node.js `vm` module, `semver` package, `better-sqlite3` for reviews persistence, `vitest` for tests.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Plugin Registry Module\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/registry/index.ts`\n- Create: `src/registry/registry.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Implement the registry service**\n\n```typescript\n// src/registry/index.ts\nimport type { PluginManifest, RegistryService } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function createRegistry(): RegistryService {\n  // Map of name -> Map of version -> manifest\n  const plugins = new Map<string, Map<string, PluginManifest>>();\n\n  return {\n    register(manifest: PluginManifest): void {\n      if (!plugins.has(manifest.name)) {\n        plugins.set(manifest.name, new Map());\n      }\n      plugins.get(manifest.name)!.set(manifest.version, { ...manifest });\n    },\n\n    get(name: string): PluginManifest | null {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions || versions.size === 0) return null;\n      // Return the latest registered version\n      const allVersions = Array.from(versions.keys());\n      const latest = allVersions[allVersions.length - 1];\n      return versions.get(latest)! ;\n    },\n\n    getVersion(name: string, version: string): PluginManifest | null {\n      return plugins.get(name)?.get(version) ?? null;\n    },\n\n    list(): PluginManifest[] {\n      const result: PluginManifest[] = [];\n      for (const versions of plugins.values()) {\n        for (const manifest of versions.values()) {\n          result.push(manifest);\n        }\n      }\n      return result;\n    },\n\n    search(query: string): PluginManifest[] {\n      const q = query.toLowerCase();\n      const result: PluginManifest[] = [];\n      for (const versions of plugins.values()) {\n        for (const manifest of versions.values()) {\n          if (\n            manifest.name.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||\n            manifest.description.toLowerCase().includes(q)\n          ) {\n            result.push(manifest);\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      return result;\n    },\n\n    remove(name: string, version: string): boolean {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions) return false;\n      const deleted = versions.delete(version);\n      if (versions.size === 0) plugins.delete(name);\n      return deleted;\n    },\n\n    listVersions(name: string): string[] {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions) return [];\n      return Array.from(versions.keys());\n    },\n\n    update(name: string, version: string, updates: Partial<PluginManifest>): void {\n      const versions = plugins.get(name);\n      if (!versions) throw new Error(`Plugin ${name} not found`);\n      const existing = versions.get(version);\n      if (!existing) throw new Error(`Version ${version} of ${name} not found`);\n      versions.set(version, { ...existing, ...updates, name, version });\n    },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Write tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/registry/registry.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { createRegistry } from './index.js';\nimport type { PluginManifest } from '../types.js';\n\nconst makeManifest = (overrides: Partial<PluginManifest> = {}): PluginManifest => ({\n  name: 'test-plugin',\n  version: '1.0.0',\n  description: 'A test plugin',\n  author: 'tester',\n  dependencies: {},\n  entryPoint: 'module.exports = 42;',\n  permissions: [],\n  ...overrides,\n});\n\ndescribe('RegistryService', () => {\n  let registry: ReturnType<typeof createRegistry>;\n\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    registry = createRegistry();\n  });\n\n  it('registers and retrieves a plugin', () => {\n    const manifest = makeManifest();\n    registry.register(manifest);\n    expect(registry.get('test-plugin')).toEqual(manifest);\n  });\n\n  it('returns null for unknown plugin', () => {\n    expect(registry.get('nope')).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('gets a specific version', () => {\n    registry.register(makeManifest({ version: '1.0.0' }));\n    registry.register(makeManifest({ version: '2.0.0' }));\n    expect(registry.getVersion('test-plugin', '1.0.0')?.version).toBe('1.0.0');\n  });\n\n  it('lists all plugins', () => {\n    registry.register(makeManifest({ name: 'a', version: '1.0.0' }));\n    registry.register(makeManifest({ name: 'b', version: '1.0.0' }));\n    expect(registry.list()).toHaveLength(2);\n  });\n\n  it('searches by name and description', () => {\n    registry.register(makeManifest({ name: 'logger', description: 'Logging tool' }));\n    registry.register(makeManifest({ name: 'auth', description: 'Auth service' }));\n    expect(registry.search('log')).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(registry.search('service')).toHaveLength(1);\n  });\n\n  it('removes a plugin version', () => {\n    registry.register(makeManifest());\n    expect(registry.remove('test-plugin', '1.0.0')).toBe(true);\n    expect(registry.get('test-plugin')).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('returns false when removing nonexistent', () => {\n    expect(registry.remove('nope', '1.0.0')).toBe(false);\n  });\n\n  it('lists versions', () => {\n    registry.register(makeManifest({ version: '1.0.0' }));\n    registry.register(makeManifest({ version: '2.0.0' }));\n    expect(registry.listVersions('test-plugin')).toEqual(['1.0.0', '2.0.0']);\n  });\n\n  it('updates a plugin', () => {\n    registry.register(makeManifest());\n    registry.update('test-plugin', '1.0.0', { description: 'Updated' });\n    expect(registry.get('test-plugin')?.description).toBe('Updated');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 3: Run tests**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/registry/registry.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Version Resolver Module\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/resolver/index.ts`\n- Create: `src/resolver/resolver.test.ts`\n\nUses semver npm package for all version resolution.\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Sandboxed Runner Module\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/runner/index.ts`\n- Create: `src/runner/runner.test.ts`\n\nUses Node.js `vm` module. Enforces timeouts. Returns structured SandboxResult.\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Review System Module\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/reviews/index.ts`\n- Create: `src/reviews/reviews.test.ts`\n\nUses better-sqlite3 for persistence. Supports flagging, average ratings excluding flagged.\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Dependency Graph Module\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/deps/index.ts`\n- Create: `src/deps/deps.test.ts`\n\nBuilds dependency trees, detects cycles, topological sort, flatten.\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Integration Layer\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `src/index.test.ts`\n\nExports `createMarketplace()` composing all modules. Implements `installPlugin()` workflow.\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Final Validation\n\nRun:\n- `npm run build`\n- `npm run lint`\n- `npm test`\n\nFix any issues.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":119,"cache_read_input_tokens":22382,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":119},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f152d743-